10/05/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The main opposition Social Democratic Party (SDP) re-elected Chairman Ivica Racan at its conference Saturday (8 May).
Racan, who served as prime minister in the previous government, left office in December.
Former Defence Minister Zeljka Antunovic was elected his deputy Saturday.
Following his re-election, Racan said the party is heading in a new direction and would focus on next year's local elections.
(Vecernji List, Vjesnik - 10/05/04;
HINA, AFP - 08/05/04)
